statements.statement: You understand that identity ownership is crucial in decentralized systems.
You believe centralized identity management is more secure than decentralized approaches.
You regularly verify your digital identity before interacting with services online.
You think it's unnecessary to verify your identity when transacting online.
You are aware of the importance of cryptographic keys for managing your identity.
You feel that passwords alone are enough to manage your online identity.
You understand the risks of relying solely on third parties for identity verification.
You believe third parties are always trustworthy for managing your identity.
You actively manage your identity credentials across multiple devices.
You don't see the need to manage identity credentials on different devices.
You understand that cryptographic proofs are crucial for identity assertions.
You believe that identity assertions can be trusted without cryptographic proofs.
You ensure that your identity data is securely stored using decentralized methods.
You store your identity data in easily accessible, centralized locations.
You understand the importance of being able to revoke identity credentials.
You believe identity credentials do not need to be revocable once issued.
You regularly audit your digital identity and associated credentials.
You think auditing your identity credentials is unnecessary.
You are proactive in ensuring your digital identity remains under your control.
You don't take any special actions to keep control over your digital identity.
